The course gives an overview about the archaeological and written sources of the history and religion of the ancient Egypt,  also, of the political history, main features of the mythology, pantheon and cults of the ancient Egypt in his historical development. Much illustrative material will be used.

NB! Classroom teaching is only in Estonian.
Written exam papers can be submitted in English, Russian or German if the student's mother tongue is not EObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce the originality of the material and spiritual culture of the ancient Egyptians, the common and different cultural characteristics in comparison to the neighboring cultures, as well to give a systematic overview about the sources, main features of the mythology, pantheon and cults of the religion of  the ancient  Egypt.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student has a systematic knowledge about the sources, main features of the mythology, pantheon and cults of the religion of  the ancient Egypt.  He/she will know this learnings to associate in the larger context of the ancient religions and, in general, in context of the religious history;  also, will to put of use at studying of the other disciplines of religious history in the future.
